{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Fees & Trade Costs\n",
    "\n",
    "[![Open In Colab](https://colab.research.google.com/assets/colab-badge.svg)](https://colab.research.google.com/github/MiniXC/simple-back/blob/master/docs/intro/fees.ipynb)\n",
    "\n",
    "Some strategies can fall apart when broker commissions are taken into account. The `FlatPerFee` and `FlatPerShare` fees come with simple-back, but you can define your own fees by extending the `Fee` class."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%%capture\n",
    "!pip install --upgrade simple_back"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from simple_back.backtester import BacktesterBuilder\n",
    "\n",
    "builder = (\n",
    "   BacktesterBuilder()\n",
    "   .name('AAPL without Fees')\n",
    "   .balance(10_000)\n",
    "   .calendar('NYSE')\n",
    "   .compare(['AAPL'])\n",
    "   .live_progress()\n",
    "   .live_plot()\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x468 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "bt = builder.build()\n",
    "for day, event, b in bt['2015-1-1':'2020-1-1']:\n",
    "    b.pf.liquidate()\n",
    "    b.long('AAPL', percent=1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Flat Fees"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "As you can see, selling & buying AAPL at every open and close results in the same as simply buying it once and holding it. But for many brokers, this is not realistic. Let's assume we have to pay a flat commission of 1 dollar per trade. We can do this using `FlatPerTrade`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x468 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from simple_back.fees import FlatPerTrade\n",
    "\n",
    "bt = (\n",
    "    builder\n",
    "    .name('AAPL (fee per trade)')\n",
    "    .trade_cost(FlatPerTrade(1))\n",
    "    .build()\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "for day, event, b in bt['2015-1-1':'2020-1-1']:\n",
    "    b.pf.liquidate()\n",
    "    b.long('AAPL', percent=1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can also assume a flat commission of 5 cents per share."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x468 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from simple_back.fees import FlatPerShare\n",
    "\n",
    "bt = (\n",
    "    builder\n",
    "    .name('AAPL (fee per share)')\n",
    "    .trade_cost(FlatPerShare(.05))\n",
    "    .build()\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "for day, event, b in bt['2015-1-1':'2020-1-1']:\n",
    "    b.pf.liquidate()\n",
    "    b.long('AAPL', percent=1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Custom Fees\n",
    "Let's now build a custom `Fee` that charges a percentage of the total cost."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from simple_back.fees import Fee"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class PercentageFee(Fee):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def __init__(self, fee_percent):\n",
    "        self.fee_percent = fee_percent\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def nshares(self, price, capital):\n",
    "        return (capital * (1/(1 + self.fee_percent))) // price\n",
    "\n",
    "    def cost(self, price, nshares):\n",
    "        return price * nshares * (1 + self.fee_percent)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "For testing we can treat our `Fee` object like a callable."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{'nshares': 66.0, 'total': 990.0, 'fee': 330.0}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 7,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "PercentageFee(.5)(price=10,capital=1000)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The above means that when we have a security with price 10 and our capital is 1000, we can buy 66 shares for a total of 990 and of that 990, 330 will be fees."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now, we can use our `PercentageFee` in our backtest."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x468 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "bt = (\n",
    "    builder\n",
    "    .name('AAPL (fee per share)')\n",
    "    .trade_cost(PercentageFee(.0005)) # 0.05 % \n",
    "    .build()\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "for day, event, b in bt['2015-1-1':'2020-1-1']:\n",
    "    b.pf.liquidate()\n",
    "    b.long('AAPL', percent=1)"
   ]
  },
  {

   "metadata": {},
